<h2>Comments: The Meaningless Words of Everquest</h2>

<p class="posted"><strong>Posted by <a href="mailto&#58;wyldrose&#64;wolf-web&#46;com">Wyldrose</a> at September 13, 2004 09:30 AM</strong></p>
<p>Yet these words bring up powerful images to all of us.  EQ has its own language that we use everyday.  They are not meaningless words, they are words that trigger an emotional reaction.</p>

<p>I agree it is important to give details. Players come from across the globe, there are very few words that mean the same thing to everyone.  It would be nice if everyone posted messages in detailed proper english and not use 'dewd speak' or terms that someone from outside the game would not understand.</p>

<p>The same word means different things depending on server, guild, class, age, etc...  SoE and Varant made 1000s of changes to the game all of which changed the meaning of the terms we use.  </p>

<p>The list of meaningless words in EQ could fill a book.  The same can be said for the English language.  </p>

<p>It is just important that we communicate!  If something needs to be clairified than say 'I don't understand what you mean by Uber'</p>

<p>Picking at what people say or correcting them on syntax just drives people apart.  Look for the meaning of what they say.. not how they say it.</p>

<p>-Wyldrose Spirithealer<br />
