<p class="posted"><strong>Posted by <a href="mailto&#58;fazool&#64;hotmail&#46;com">Ethyre</a> at January 26, 2005 02:57 PM</strong></p>
<p>I agree with 4 of 5.</p>

<p>Mudflation (when used properly) is actually a very specific description of a certin phenomenon.</p>

<p>In EQ, there is an infinite supply of material wealth into the economy (no matter how many times you kill that mob, they keep spawning with armloads of loot and cash).  There is no attrition (loot never wears out or breaks).</p>

<p>Basically, the longer we play, the more "stuff" gets passed around either as gear or as plat (from vendors who buy our loot).</p>

<p>Mudflation describes the negative side-effects of this infinite-supply situation.</p>

<p>Mudflation implies that there is too much inflation in a multi user dungeon because the economy is imbalanced.</p>

